{{nihongo|'''''Badlands'''''|バッドランズ}} is a [[LaserDisc]] arcade video game developed by [[Konami]] and published by both Konami and [[Centuri]]. It debuted at the [[Arcade game#Amusement & Music Operators Association|Amusement and Music Operators Association]] show in October 1983 and was released to the public in early 1984.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sharpe |first1=Roger C. |title=The Most Exciting Video... Pinball's Return... Video Jukebox's Appeal |magazine=[[Play Meter]] |date=January 15, 1984 |volume=10 |issue=2 |pages=63–6 |url=https://archive.org/details/play-meter-volume-10-number-2-january-15th-1984/Play%20Meter%20-%20Volume%2010%2C%20Number%202%20-%20January%2015th%201984/page/63}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Badlands (Registration Number PAu000573225) |url=https://cocatalog.loc.gov |access-date=30 August 2021 |website=[[United States Copyright Office]]}}</ref> ''Badlands'' follows a [[cowboy]] named Buck seeking vengeance on a gang of outlaws and its leader, Landolf, for the murder of his wife and children.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Badlands (1984) |url=https://www.mobygames.com/game/badlands_ |access-date=2022-10-13 |website=MobyGames}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Badlands'' is an [[interactive movie]] set in a [[American frontier|wild west]] fantasy world.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Badlands (1984) |url=https://www.mobygames.com/game/badlands_ |access-date=2022-10-13 |website=MobyGames}}</ref> The arcade controls consist of one large "shoot" button. Gameplay consists of video scenes, requiring players to shoot and react to environmental hazards and enemies. The player starts with 3 lives and losing all lives ends the game. The objective is to eliminate outlaws and claim their bounties.

== Reception ==
In Japan, ''Game Machine'' listed ''Badlands'' on their September 15, 1984, issue as the second most-successful upright arcade unit of the month.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Game Machine's Best Hit Games 25 - アップライト, コックピット型TVゲーム機 (Upright/Cockpit Videos)|magazine=[[:ja:ゲームマシン|Game Machine]]|issue=244|publisher=[[:ja:アミューズメント通信社|Amusement Press, Inc.]]|date=15 September 1984|page=31|lang=ja}}</ref>

